Last fix I swear Can we wrap this in a `createEffect`?

```ts
createEffect(() => {
    const unsubscribe = mutationCache().subscribe(() => {
    const nextResult = replaceEqualDeep(
      result(),
      getResult(mutationCache(), options()),
    )
    if (result() !== nextResult) {
      setResult(nextResult)
    }
  })

  onCleanup(unsubscribe)
})
```

The reason to do this is that if the `options` object changes in the client code. We should run the sub function with the new `options`

For example:
```ts
// First render
const [count, setCount] = createSignal(0)

const mutationState = useMutationState(() => ({
  mutationKey: ['mutation', count()] // count() is 0
}))
```

```ts
// When count is updated to 2
const [count, setCount] = createSignal(0)

const mutationState = useMutationState(() => ({
  mutationKey: ['mutation', count()] // count() is 2
}))

// This will work now!!!
```
